-- Thomas Cook’s Indian Unit Gets Buyout Bids, Sunday Times Reports
-- B y   P a t r i c i a   K u o
-- 2012-03-18T08:58:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-18/thomas-cook-s-indian-unit-gets-buyout-bids-sunday-times-reports.html
Thomas Cook Group Plc (TCG) ,  Europe ’s
second-largest tour operator, is getting interest from buyout
firms including Carlyle Group LP and KKR & Co. for its Indian
currency-exchange business, the Sunday Times reported, without
saying where it obtained the information.  As many as 10 bidders are vying for the unit, which has a
market value of 167 million pounds ($265 million), according to
the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patricia Kuo in London at 
